<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Before this study, 83 species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Brulle, 1846" authorityName="Brulle" authorityYear="1846" class="Insecta" family="Stephanidae" genus="Megischus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Megischus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Megischus</taxonomicName>
were known worldwide, of which 3 species were known from China. In this paper, these three species of the genus are listed from China. A key to species of the genus 
